parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling can cause the loss of power steering and braking, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
especially during deceleration and acceleration
and may not restart for at least an hour. The electrical system remains operational
but power steering and braking are lost.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause the passenger side of the windshield defroster and passenger window defroster to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The heater blows cold air on the passenger side
while the driver side blows warm or hot air. The passenger side windshield defroster and window defroster do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission/throttle positioning sensor issues can cause the vehicle to jerk or lurch forward unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly jerks or lurches forward without warning
especially when accelerating or decelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience various warning lights, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
loses power
warning lights illuminate
electrical failures
and issues with the throttle body
alternator
and battery.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause the vehicle to blow cold air, reducing visibility and creating a safety hazard, especially in cold weather.
symptoms: The vehicle blows cold air
only blows hot air on the driver's side
and has issues with defrosting and defogging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake light stays on
the vehicle experiences issues with the brake switch sensor
and has problems with the brake pads and rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Bag and Seat Belt Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag and seat belt system can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The air bag light stays on
the seat belts do not function properly
and the vehicle experiences issues with the passenger side air bag.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window and lock system can cause inconvenience and safety issues, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The windows do not function properly
the locks do not unlock
and the vehicle experiences issues with the electronic door locks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Bag and Seat Belt Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag and seat belt system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The air bag warning light is illuminated
the air bags do not deploy in a crash
the seat belts do not tighten or restrain properly
and the vehicle may experience a loss of air bag and seat belt pretensioner deployment capability in certain crash events.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can lead to loss of control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The brakes may skip or pulse before stopping
the vehicle may stall
and the brakes may not engage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Column and Heating System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column and heating system can lead to loss of control of the vehicle and discomfort for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The steering column may make a noise
the heating system may make a noise
and the vehicle may experience a popping or clunking sound when driving.
